    <caption><emphasis effect="bold">The Spectra fiber used to make the bulletproof vests used by police and military is made of ultra-high-molecular-weight polyethylene, a simple alkene polymer.</emphasis> (credit: modification of work “US Navy 081028-N-3857R-007 Seabees participate in a chemical, biological and radiological warfare drill” by U.S. Navy photo by Mass Communication Specialist 1st Class Chad Runge/Wikimedia Commons, Public Domain)</caption>
